    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>Measuring mass segregation and the core mass distribution of SDC335</prj:name>
        <prj:note>There are two primary goals to this project: 1) Testing the global collapse scenario described in the previous section by searching for primordial mass segregation; 2)  Establishing, for the first time, the shape of the core mass function in an OB cluster progenitor. Outcome of goal # 1 will confirm or infirm the global collapse scenario for massive stars, while outcome of goal # 2 will tell us if the CMF in SDC335 is compatible with a universal IMF on the scale of individual OB cluster progenitors. To achieve these goals, we propose to map the SDC335 OB cluster progenitor in dust continuum at 1.4mm, an look for two temperature gas tracers. </prj:note>
